Package: ViralEntropR
Title: A Computational Pipeline for Entropy-Informed Detection of Emerging Viral Variants
Version: 0.5.1
Authors@R: c(
              person("Vadim", "Tyuryaev", ,"vadim.tyuryaev@gmail.com", 
                      role = c("aut", "cre"), 
                      comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0008-1361-6265")),
              person("Jane", "Heffernan", , "jmheffer@yorku.ca", 
                      role = c("aut")),
              person("Hanna", "Jankowski", , "hkj@yorku.ca", 
                      role = c("aut"))
             )
Description: Implements an entropy-informed pipeline for detecting
    emerging variants in viral amino acid sequence data, extending
    prior clustering-based approaches, including hemagglutinin
    clustering methods (Li et al., 2015)
    <doi:10.1142/9789814667944_0018>. The approach combines Gower
    distance (Gower, 1971) <doi:10.2307/2528823> for categorical
    sequence data, Partitioning Around Medoids clustering (Kaufman
    and Rousseeuw, 1990) <doi:10.1002/9780470316801>, Hellinger
    distance (van der Vaart, 1998) <doi:10.1017/CBO9780511802256>
    for quantifying temporal distributional shifts, and
    nonparametric multivariate change-point detection based on
    energy statistics (Matteson and James, 2014)
    <doi:10.1080/01621459.2013.849605> via 'ecp', with optional
    wild binary segmentation (Fryzlewicz, 2014)
    <doi:10.1214/14-AOS1245> via 'HDcpDetect'. A FASTA preprocessing
    toolkit supports header parsing, ambiguous-residue filtering,
    integer encoding, and temporal partitioning into expanding,
    sliding, or disjoint windows. Mutation frequency tables and
    Shannon entropy trajectory plots characterise sequence
    composition and evolutionary dynamics across time. A curated
    dataset of SARS-CoV-2 Variants of Concern and Variants of
    Interest with associated metadata is included, along with a
    bundled NCBI Spike protein sample and vignettes demonstrating
    the full workflow.
